<h6 class="kicker"><a href="//dealbook.blogs.nytimes.com/category/ipoofferings/">I.P.O./OFFERINGS &#187;</a></h6>
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Biomet Chooses Banks for I.P.O. <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Biomet, a medical device unit that was taken private by private equity firms in 2007 for $11.4 billion, is said to have selected Bank of America Merrill Lynch, Goldman Sachs and JPMorgan Chase as the lead underwriters for the companyâs initial public offering, expected this year, Reuters writes, citing unidentified people familiar with the situation.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/26/us-biomet-ipo-idUSBREA1P1Y020140226"> REUTERS </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Foreign Banksâ Share of Chinaâs I.P.O. Market Hits 5-Year High <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Foreign investment banksâ securities joint ventures have underwritten 8 percent of the initial public offerings in China so far this year, a five-year high, The Wall Street Journal reports.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304709904579406510963375556?mg=reno64-wsj"> WALL STREET JOURNAL </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story --></div>
